<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>If destination directory is not set, Zend_File should assume that the destination directory is the same one that is returned by PHP function sys_get_temp_dir().</p>

<p>This way is you use Rename Filter for moving the file to the final location after the upload you do not need to call setDestionation() on the element.</p>

<p>In case you are rendering a form with a file element that doesn't have destination set throws: "Warning: Exception caught by form: "file_element_name" not found by file transfer adapter"</p>

    </div>
